Protocols/WebServiceNetworkInterface.htm.name: loadResource(resource:completion:)
Protocols/WebServiceNetworkInterface.htm.abstract: Implement this method to tell a WebService what to do when .load() is called on it’s NetworkResource. The NetworkResource on which the .load() method is called comes in as an argument, and any networking library can be used to fire the resource’s internal request over the network, and then a NetworkResponse can be created from the internet’s response, and passed into the completion closure.

Protocols/WebServiceNetworkInterface.htm.name: WebServiceNetworkInterface
Protocols/WebServiceNetworkInterface.htm.abstract: WebServiceNetworkInterface: A protocol which lets any object become a bridge between a webservice and the internet.

Protocols/WebService.html.name: WebService
Protocols/WebService.html.abstract: WebService is a protocol which helps you write your network requests in a declarative, type-safe and expressive way.
